<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="408" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,885,1164]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,957,983]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by the rounded apex of the aedeagus with a very short apical spine (more easily seen at high magnification and in ventral view). In 
<collectingCountry box="[891,986,993,1019]" name="Pakistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
material there is a pair of dark patches posteriorly on the vertex and a sub-brachypterous female form (
<figureCitation box="[861,1001,1029,1055]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,424,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-123@8.[151,1436,417,1826]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Maiestas species. A–E, M. subviridis (Metcalf) (after Khatri &amp; Webb, 2010) A–B: habitus (macropterus and subbrachypterus respectively), dorsal view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: aedeagus, lateral view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F–L, M. pruthii (Metcalf) (after Dash &amp; Viraktamath, 1998) F: habitus, dorsal view; G: habitus, lateral view; H: face; I: style, dorsal view; J: connective and aedeagus, ventral view; K; apex of aedeagus, lateral view; L: connective and aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5635924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5635924/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Figs 4A, 4B</figureCitation>
); for details, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Khatri I. &amp; Webb, M. D." pageId="7" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref7812" refString="Khatri I., &amp; Webb, M. D. (2010) The Deltocephalinae leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa, 2365 (1), 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2365.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Khatri &amp; Webb, 2010: 11</bibRefCitation>
. The material listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Khatri I. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[446,701,1065,1091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref7812" refString="Khatri I., &amp; Webb, M. D. (2010) The Deltocephalinae leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa, 2365 (1), 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2365.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Khatri &amp; Webb (2010)</bibRefCitation>
was collected on 11.v.07, not 28.viii.07 (paddy), as stated. These authors also figured a specimen from Guddo Barrage with a somewhat more elongate aedeagus but it is difficult to judge whether this specimen is the same species as now only the genitalia remain (BMNH).
</paragraph>
